<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kai</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">For those that haven't read all of the long thread on EMUs, go read it for some good info and to figure out who I am.<p>Now that that is cleared up, lets start off with some good idea, bad idea.<p>Good Idea<br>14 ppl who know what they are doing working on one emulator<p>Bad Idea<br>4 groups of 4 ppl each working on 4 emulators<p>Does everyone agree? Good.  So, intro-abduction time.  My name is Kai.  I am NOT a programmer.  I can debug, sort, and modify other peoples code, but I couldn't fresh code my way out of a wet paper sack.  What I can do is be an asshole.  I am in RL the pres. of a software group (we don't like the name company... reminds us of suits).  Besides designing a game right now we are also programming consultants for other software companies trying to write games.  I am just a manager. And that's Mr. Manager to you slimes :).<p>Like I said in the other thread, I am making a new site for my group and we are hoping to get the other groups to join into one task force.  From what I have seen we are very close to having a "working" EMU.  I know that is going to haunt me, so let me explain to the newbies.  This does not mean we are close to offline playing.  That may never happen.  But I think we are close to having a beta EMU that could at least do simple functions.<p>Before I ramble my fingers off, I wanna hear from the others that are working on this project and get their thoughts.<p>Kai<p>
